UI consistency rules (design system):

All UI components must follow a single, coherent visual system.

Use these project primitives:
- Colors and typography from constants/theme (Colors, FontSizes).
- NativeWind/Tailwind for spacing, layout, radii and sizing.
- Consistent spacing scale (prefer Tailwind spacing classes; avoid ad-hoc numbers).
- Consistent corner radius (prefer the same rounded values across cards/buttons).
- Consistent shadows (use the same shadow approach across surfaces).
- Consistent press/hover feedback (opacity or subtle background change).

Do NOT introduce one-off visual styles per component.
Before adding a new style pattern, reuse an existing component/pattern or propose a shared primitive.
